p.span: The Hancock Central School District will be closed through May 15, 2020.

br.span: HCSD will deliver no-cost breakfast and lunch to all of its students

a.span: Click here for the latest information on Coronavirus and our District.

div.h3: We nurture and empower each learner’s unlimited capacity to become a responsible citizen with a promising future.

li.a: Title I: Parent Right to Know

span.p: Governor Andrew Cuomo has extended NYS on PAUSE through May 15, 2020, meaning all schools will be closed through May 15. Click for more information.

h3.a: The College Board cancels June SAT

span.div: The College Board announced Wednesday, April 15, that it has canceled the administration of June 6 SAT and SAT Subject Tests. Click for more information.

h3.a: June Regents canceled; student requirements modified

span.p: The New York State Education Department has announced the cancellation of the June 2020 administration of Regents Exams and released guidance on modifications to requirements for students to graduate and earn their high school diplomas, credentials and endorsements. Click to read more.

h3.a: NY State of Health - Letter to Families

span.div: New York families may be eligible for health coverage with financial assistance through NY State of Health due to their loss of coverage and income. Click for more information.

span.p: Gov. Andrew Cuomo has issued an Executive Order that postpones all school budget votes and Board of Education elections until at least June 1. Click for more information.
